    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "Not sure if this is related, but if I render pavement with sprite offset using:\r\n\r\n```csharp\r\nvar s = theater.TileSprite(tile);\r\ndirty[cell] = new Sprite(s.Sheet, s.Bounds, s.ZRamp, s.Offset, s.Channel, s.BlendMode);\r\n```\r\n\r\nunits will go through it when entering the cell:\r\n\r\n![openra-2018-09-18t134705570z](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/756669/45692118-4d1d0b80-bb5a-11e8-9105-1a25c81fb4a5.png)\r\n\r\nSetting the offset to zero:\r\n\r\n```csharp\r\ndirty[cell] = new Sprite(s.Sheet, s.Bounds, s.ZRamp, float2.Zero, s.Channel, s.BlendMode);\r\n```\r\n\r\nbreaks rendering of the pavement:\r\n\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/756669/45692194-7d64aa00-bb5a-11e8-97b2-b3b145a1f056.png)\r\n"
  },
