    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "And the first screenshot, where you have ZScale 0 and a positive ZOffset, is defining this situation:\r\n![hiding](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/167819/45694624-9029af80-bb57-11e8-8d5a-558318971436.png)\r\n\r\nThe concrete layer is tilted, but pulled closer to the camera.   This pulls it in front of the tank, hiding the bottom part of it (from the perspective of the camera).\r\n\r\nEdit: This has the same backwards z-coordinate as above."
